From 0eb0e1dd8ba57ca3b8a32c394d7d853dc3ed275d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: 3DStreet <3dstreet@local>
Date: Tue, 2 Jun 2026 21:33:05 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Parallelize bhatt_lod grid population and tree output walk
 with rayon

* Initial grid population (per-level cells map) parallelizes via fold+reduce
  over per-thread hashmaps, gated by PAR_GRID_THRESHOLD=4096 to keep small
  inputs on the sequential path.

* recurse_to_output refactored to collect mutations (set_to_output,
  set_children, clear_children) during a &TA-only parallel walk, then
  apply them sequentially after. Order-preserving par_iter keeps new_children
  byte-identical to the sequential walk.

* compute_lod_tree gains TA: Sync; the only build-lod call site
  (process_file_lod_tsplat) gains the matching bound.
